messages.title: A HUNG PARLIAMENT WOULD MEAN 5 MORE YEARS OF GORDON BROWN.
messages.content: A hung parliament would mean Gordon Brown would stay as Prime Minister, and Britain needs energy and leadership to make sure that does not happen. The way to ensure we don't have 5 more years of Brown is to vote Conservative.

mentions.tacticalSituation: The leaflet suggests that a hung parliament will result in Gordon Brown staying as Prime Minister for five more years, which can be interpreted as a call for tactical voting to prevent this outcome.

issues.governance: The leaflet suggests that Gordon Brown staying in power in a hung parliament is not desirable, implying a need for a change in governance.

leaflet.personalStatement: David Cameron expresses his commitment to bringing change and optimism and highlights the need for energy, leadership, and new ideas.

images.caption: David Cameron signing a document with the text 'A PERSONAL MESSAGE FROM DAVID CAMERON' visible.

leaflet.additionalNotes: The leaflet focuses on the implications of a hung parliament and advocates for a Conservative vote to prevent Gordon Brown from continuing as Prime Minister.
